decompress

(2001-01-30)

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: decompress \decompress\ v. i. to undergo the process of {decompression}. [PJC]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: decompress \decompress\ v. t. to subject to the process of {decompression}. [PJC]

decompress v 1: restore to its uncompressed form; "decompress data" [syn: {uncompress}] [ant: {compress}] 2: decrease the pressure of; "depressurize the cabin in the air plane" [syn: {depressurize}, {depressurise}] [ant: {pressurize}, {pressurize}] 3: become less tense, rest, or take one's ease; "He relaxed in the hot tub"; "Let's all relax after a hard day's work" [syn: {relax}, {loosen up}, {unbend}, {unwind}, {slow down}] [ant: {tense}]
